And I said C, 2016 is gotta be right.

102
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,439
Well, do you wanna hear the story?

103
00:04:40,439 --> 00:04:45,519
Interestingly, the term was coined in 1996 in the book Fight Club,

104
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:50,199
but it was in 2016 that it was one of the dictionaries words of the year.

105
00:04:50,199 --> 00:04:52,839
Now, let's review our words of the day.

106
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:54,439
First, there is offense.

107
00:04:54,439 --> 00:04:59,359
People can take offense and be offended by something that is offensive,

108
00:04:59,359 --> 00:05:03,479
something that is offensive could be rude, insulting and shocking.

109
00:05:03,479 --> 00:05:08,479
It might take the form of humiliation or discrimination against a person or group.

110
00:05:08,479 --> 00:05:11,199
The term snowflake is a word used by some people

111
00:05:11,199 --> 00:05:15,000
to talk about other people who they think get offended too easily

112
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,639
and unnecessarily.

113
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:21,800
They don't want to change their language or ideas just because snowflakes get upset.

114
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,759
Then we had the word invoke.

115
00:05:23,759 --> 00:05:29,199
If you invoke something, you use it as a reason to explain your actions and feelings.

116
00:05:29,199 --> 00:05:34,480
To call something out is to challenge it, to highlight it and look for justification.

117
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,279
And finally, we have taboo.

118
00:05:36,279 --> 00:05:39,560
Something that society says is offensive and shocking.

119
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,519
So there we have it.

120
00:05:40,519 --> 00:05:42,720
What do you think Rob of this topic?

121
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:45,080
Well, it's a very difficult subject,

122
